The Marvel Cinematic Universe
Melanoma is a highly concerning form of skin cancer, with varying survival rates based on the stage of the disease. According to the American Cancer Society, the 5-year relative survival rates for melanoma skin cancer are over 99% for localized cases, 71% for regional cases, and 32% for distant cases. Melanoma originates in the melanocytes, the cells that produce skin pigment, and can be identified by changes in existing moles or the development of new, unusual-looking growths on the skin The purpose of this analysis is to investigate the survival of patients who have undergone surgery to remove malignant melanoma tumors. The study, which includes 205 patients, aims to uncover patterns in patients’ characteristics and health conditions following the tumor removal over the study’s duration.
